{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d12516d7-6755-4322-a8a5-b3943b93d82e","content":"Your project uses **xUnit v3 on Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (MTP) — indicated by `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. With MTP, xUnit v3 uses its own native filter syntax via `--filter-query`.\n\nHowever, since you want a **single combined `--filter` expression for `dotnet test`**, use the MTP-compatible filter syntax:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName~Integration & Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**Breakdown:**\n- `ClassName~Integration` — class name *contains* \"Integration\"\n- `Category=Smoke` — matches `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]`\n- `&` — both conditions must be true\n\nMake sure your smoke tests are decorated with:\n```csharp\n[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"71e5b6b8-d547-4614-b0a8-1291e97ca64c","outputTokens":197,"requestId":"BD0A:147F4E:21C0CFB:265803D:6A07E177"},"id":"b5d72ef9-bd86-4881-aaca-8032e976d4f4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:16:16.047Z","parentId":"f92ee50d-8ae4-4369-8b97-a88a92795140"}
